# Python virtualenv

All Python in this repo must run through `.venv`. System/`py`/`python` on PATH often lacks project packages (`speech_to_speech`, `buddy_tools` deps, etc.) and causes `ModuleNotFoundError`.

## Required

Prefer the venv interpreter directly (reliable in agent shells; do not rely on prior `activate`):

```powershell
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pytest tests/ -x
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -c "from speech_to_speech.pipeline import events"
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pip show speech-to-speech
```

On Unix-style shells in the same repo:

```bash
.venv/bin/python -m pytest tests/ -x
```

## Do not

- Run bare `python`, `python3`, or `py` for project code, tests, or import probes
- Assume a previous turn activated the venv (each Shell call may be a fresh session)
- Use `activate && python ...` as the primary pattern — activation is easy to skip and flaky across shells; call `.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe` instead

## If `.venv` is missing

Tell the user and point them at README setup (`python -m venv .venv`, then `.\setup-venv.ps1`). Do not invent a system-Python workaround for imports.
